Executive Profile
Robert D. Isom Jr.President, American Airlines Group Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 6 different industries.53$6,552,114As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Robert D. Isom Jr. has been President of American Airlines Group Inc. since August 29, 2016 and American Airlines Inc. since September 2, 2016. Mr. Isom oversees American’s operations, planning, marketing, sales, alliances and pricing. He served as the Chief Operating Officer of American Airlines Group Inc. from December 2013 to August 29, 2016. Mr. Isom served as the Chief Operating Officer of American Airlines Inc. since December 2013 until September 2, 2016 and ... served as Executive Vice President until September 2, 2016. He served as an Executive Vice President of American Airlines Group Inc. from December 2013 to August 29, 2016. He served as the Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President of US Airways, LLC (formerly, America West Airlines Inc.) since June 6, 2007. He served as Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President of US Airways Group, Inc. since December 9, 2013. Mr. Isom served as Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President of US Airways Inc. since September 10, 2007 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from December 2013 to August 29, 2016. He was responsible for all aspects of airline operations, including customer service, flight operations, maintenance, regional carrier management, cargo, safety and security. Mr. Isom served as Chief Restructuring Officer of GMAC, LLC from October 2006 to August 2007 and as Chief Operating Officer, Residential Finance Group, GMAC ResCap from October 2005 to September 2006. He served as Senior Vice President of Customer Service at Northwest Airlines, LLC (alternate name, Northwest Airlines Corporation) since April 25, 2003. He served as Senior Vice President, Ground Operations and Customer Service of Northwest Airlines, Inc. from 2003 to 2005 and served as its Vice President of International from 2001 to 2003. In this position, he was responsible for directing all passenger, baggage and security related activities at 180 domestic and international airports. Mr. Isom served Northwest Airlines from 1991 to 1995 and from 2000 to 2001 in various positions, including Vice President of Finance and Director of Cargo Strategic Planning. From 1995 to 2000, Mr. Isom served senior management positions in finance, operations and revenue management at US Airways, LLC. He had commercial responsibility for Pacific operations outside of Japan. He was designated and elected by Northwest pursuant to the terms of the Series A Preferred Stock. From 1987 to 1989, Mr. Isom served customer service and logistics management positions at The Procter & Gamble Company. He served as a Director of US Airways Inc. He served as a Director of Pinnacle Airlines Corp. (alternate name, Pinnacle Airlines, Inc.) from August 2004 to September 12, 2005. Mr. Isom holds Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering and a Bachelor of Arts in English from the University of Notre Dame and a Master's in Business Administration degree from the University of Michigan.Read Full Background




