Robert D. Isom, Jr. 

		
		President, 

	
		 American Airlines Group Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 04/27/2017 



Executive Summary
Isom is President of American Airlines Group, a major American airline headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas. He assumed his current role in August 2016 after serving as Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of the company, following the merger between American Airlines and US Airways. 
Personal Attributes and Interests

In January 2011, Isom wrote a letter to US Airways employees, praising them for a job well done. "Safety is the number one priority at US Airways - always has been and always will be," he wrote. "All of us at US Airways m 
Current Focus

Building trust: According to an April 2017 Dallas News article, American Airlines is taking the rare step of offering a mid-contract raise to its roughly 37,000 pilots and flight attendants after months of simmering ten 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1964.
Isom earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Mechanical Engineering and a Bachelor of Arts degree in English from the University of Notre Dame. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Board of Directors, Pinnacle Airlines, Inc. (2004 - 2005)
Member, Board of Directors, St. Mary's Food Bank Alliance in Phoenix 
Donations and Philanthropy

Isom in the 2009-2010 election cycle contributed a total of $3,400 to federal candidates and causes, including $1,250 to Pennsylvania Senator Arlen Specter's unsuccessful 2010 re-election campaign (after switching parties, he was de 
 





